#: ../../H/hose.rst:5
msgid "hose"
msgstr "hose"

#: ../../H/hose.rst:7
msgid ""
"vt\\. [common] To make non-functional or greatly degraded in performance. "
"\"That big ray-tracing program really hoses the system.\" See "
":ref:`hosed`\\."
msgstr ""
"他動詞 [一般的]機能しなくする、または性能を大幅に低下させること。「あの大きなレイトレーシングプログラムは本当にシステムをhoseする」。\\ "
":ref:`hosed`\\ を参照。"

#: ../../H/hose.rst:12
msgid ""
"n\\. A narrow channel through which data flows under pressure. Generally "
"denotes data paths that represent performance bottlenecks."
msgstr "名詞 圧力の下でデータが流れる狭いチャンネル。一般に性能のボトルネックを表すデータパスを表す。"

#: ../../H/hose.rst:16
msgid ""
"n\\. Cabling, especially thick Ethernet cable. This is sometimes called bit "
"hose or hosery (play on ‘hosiery’) or ‘etherhose’. See also :ref:`washing-"
"machine`\\."
msgstr ""
"名詞 ケーブル、特に太いEthernetケーブル。これは時にbit "
"hoseやhosery(‘hosiery’のだじゃれ)、あるいは‘etherhose’と呼ばれる。\\ :ref:`washing-machine`\\"
" も参照。"
